Patch Set 1:

I have a question,

In flow diagram it is shown deactivated image can be deleted, but when I call delete image on deactivated image it is returning following error.

glance image-delete 5f0f914b-9f04-42c4-9769-07dc09e09056
u'deactivated' is not one of [u'queued', u'saving', u'active', u'killed', u'deleted', u'pending_delete']

Failed validating u'enum' in schema[u'properties'][u'status']:
    {u'description': u'Status of the image (READ-ONLY)',
     u'enum': [u'queued',
               u'saving',
               u'active',
               u'killed',
               u'deleted',
               u'pending_delete'],
     u'type': u'string'}

On instance[u'status']:
    u'deactivated'

deletion of deactivated image is allowed?
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(2 comments)

Thanks for adding this, Olena!
Minor suggestions in-line.

In the diagram I see that you have added the state transitions from 'deactivated' to 'active' and 'delete'. It think it can also go to 'pending_delete' when delayed delete is enabled.

I don't see that transition in the code either.
https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/domain/__init__.py#L114

We may have to test this on devstack.

Patch Set 1:

@Hemanth, when try to delete the deactivated image with delay-delete, it will raise an error: 
Image status transition from deactivated to pending_delete is not allowed.

So we need have a discussion about whether this behavior is ok. But at least this patch looks well in current environment.
Uploaded patch set 2.
